items.title: Man, 18, charged with child abuse material, firearm offences in Sydney
items.standfirst: T he 18-year-old was arrested after police raided a home in Matraville in the city's east yesterday.
items.content: An 18-year-old man will face court on child abuse material and firearm charges after he was arrested in Sydney's east. At about 7.45am yesterday, as part of ongoing investigations into child abuse material under Strike Force Glandore, police carried out a search warrant at a home in Matraville.Officers allegedly found a phone containing child abuse material.READ MORE: Micki thought he'd lost $150k. Then an email arrived in his inboxPolice also allegedly found two gel blasters, two imitation guns, a slingshot, two rounds of ammunition, and some cannabis.An 18-year-old man was arrested and taken to Maroubra Police Station, where he was charged with multiple child abuse material, firearm, and drug-related offences.He was refused bail to appear in court today. Investigations under Strike Force Glandore continue.DOWNLOAD THE 9NEWS APP: Stay across all the latest in breaking news, sport, politics and the weather via our news app and get notifications sent straight to your smartphone.
